---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { bySlug } from '../data/plugins';

const revlimiter = bySlug('revlimiter');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Support"
  description="Install help, activation, troubleshooting, and contact for RevLimiter and RevAudio plugins."
>
  <section class="plugin-detail">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 760px;" data-reveal>
      <h1>Support &amp; install</h1>
      <p class="pitch">
        Quick install, activation, common fixes, and how to reach us when things go sideways.
        Everything here is for <strong>RevLimiter</strong> &mdash; the only plugin shipping today.
      </p>

      <p class="status-note">
        <strong>Where things stand:</strong> RevLimiter runs as a <strong>Windows VST3</strong> plugin.
        macOS (AU) and Pro Tools (AAX) are in development &mdash; see the roadmap below. Checkout is
        reopening shortly; if you can&rsquo;t buy yet, <a href="/revlimiter#waitlist">join the waitlist</a>
        and we&rsquo;ll email you the moment it&rsquo;s live.
      </p>

      <h3>What you need</h3>
      <ul class="reqs">
        <li><strong>OS:</strong> {revlimiter?.systemReq.os ?? 'Windows 10/11 64-bit (macOS planned)'}</li>
        <li><strong>Format today:</strong> VST3 (64-bit) in any VST3 host</li>
        <li><strong>CPU / RAM:</strong> {revlimiter?.systemReq.cpu} &middot; {revlimiter?.systemReq.ram}</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="micro muted">Full specs and tested DAWs on the <a href="/revlimiter">RevLimiter page</a>.</p>

      <h3>Install (Windows VST3)</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Download the installer from the confirmation email sent to you after checkout.</li>
        <li>Run the installer and accept the licence terms.</li>
        <li>The plugin installs to <code>C:\Program Files\Common Files\VST3\</code>.</li>
        <li>Open your DAW and rescan VST3 plugins. RevLimiter appears under the <strong>RevAudio</strong> manufacturer.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Activate your licence</h3>
      <p>
        On first launch, RevLimiter asks for your licence key (the serial emailed to you right after
        checkout). Paste it in once &mdash; it&rsquo;s validated and stored locally, then reused on every
        subsequent launch.
      </p>
      <p>
        One licence covers <strong>up to 2 machines</strong> &mdash; your studio desktop and a laptop, say.
        Moving to a new machine or lost your key? Email
        <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a> with the address you purchased under
        and we&rsquo;ll sort it within one business day.
      </p>

      <h3>Platform roadmap</h3>
      <p>
        RevLimiter ships today as a <strong>Windows VST3</strong>. Two builds are in active development:
      </p>
      <ul class="roadmap">
        <li><strong>macOS (AU)</strong> &mdash; in development. If you bought on Windows, the Mac build is
          included free when it ships; we&rsquo;ll email you a download link.</li>
        <li><strong>Pro Tools (AAX)</strong> &mdash; planned. No date yet; it follows the Mac build.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Troubleshooting</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>The DAW does not see the plugin after install</summary>
        <p>
          Restart your DAW or rescan VST3 plugins. In Cubase, Studio One, Reaper, and others the rescan is
          automatic on launch but a manual refresh is sometimes needed. Confirm the .vst3 file exists at
          <code>C:\Program Files\Common Files\VST3\</code>.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>The licence key won&rsquo;t activate</summary>
        <p>
          Copy the key straight from your purchase email &mdash; no spaces before or after. Activation needs a
          live internet connection on first launch. If you&rsquo;ve already activated two machines, free one up
          or email <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a> and we&rsquo;ll reset your seats.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Crash or audio dropout</summary>
        <p>
          Send a brief email to <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a> with: DAW + version,
          OS version, sample rate + buffer size, and a description of what you were doing when it happened.
          We respond within one business day.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Mac or Pro Tools version</summary>
        <p>
          The macOS (AU) build is in development and Pro Tools (AAX) is planned &mdash; see the roadmap above.
          Buy on Windows now and the Mac build is included free when it ships. Want a heads-up the day it lands?
          <a href="/revlimiter#waitlist">Join the waitlist</a>.
        </p>
      </details>

      <h3>Contact</h3>
      <p>
        General: <a href="mailto:hello@revaudio.net">hello@revaudio.net</a><br/>
        Support: <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a><br/>
        Press: <a href="mailto:press@revaudio.net">press@revaudio.net</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .status-note {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--brass-bright);
    background: var(--bg-1);
    padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 1.75rem;
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .reqs, .roadmap {
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .reqs li, .roadmap li { margin: 0.4rem 0; }

  details {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg-1);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  details summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--brass-bright);
  }

  details[open] summary { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

  ol { color: var(--fg-dim); }
  ol li { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
</style>
